cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC

This paper deals with the measurement and classification of IPv6 addresses, which is primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI). It also involves analyzing activity logs and addressing practices, which could fall under the categories of security and cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of comprehensively probing every possible unicast IPv6 address, which could be relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
